Privacy Policy

Effective Date: March 21, 2026

This Privacy Policy describes how the CanLII Case Review app (“the App”) handles your information.

⸻

1. Overview

The App is designed to provide a streamlined way to review Canadian case law using publicly available data from CanLII.

We do not collect, sell, or share personal data for advertising or tracking purposes.

⸻

2. Information We Collect

a. User-Provided Information

The App may store information that you choose to provide, including:
	•	API settings or preferences (if applicable)
	•	Saved cases
	•	Tags, notes, or other organizational data

This information is stored locally on your device.

⸻

b. Automatically Collected Information

We do not collect personal information such as:
	•	Name
	•	Email address
	•	Location data
	•	Contacts
	•	Usage analytics tied to your identity

The App does not include third-party tracking tools or analytics frameworks.

⸻

3. How Information Is Used

Any information stored by the App is used solely to:
	•	Provide core functionality (e.g., saving cases, tracking reviewed items)
	•	Maintain your preferences and workflow within the App

We do not use your information for:
	•	Advertising
	•	Profiling
	•	Data selling or sharing

⸻

4. Data Storage

All user data (including saved cases, tags, and settings) is stored locally on your device.

We do not operate servers that store your personal data.

If you delete the App, this data will typically be deleted as well (unless backed up by your device).

⸻

5. Third-Party Services

The App retrieves case law data from CanLII (Canadian Legal Information Institute).
	•	Requests are made directly from your device to CanLII
	•	We do not intercept, store, or log this data on external servers

Your use of CanLII data may also be subject to CanLII’s own terms and policies.

⸻

6. Data Sharing

We do not share your data with any third parties.

⸻

7. Security

Because data is stored locally on your device, its security depends on your device’s security settings (e.g., passcode, encryption).

We do not transmit or store your personal data on external servers.

⸻

8. Children’s Privacy

The App is not intended for children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children.

⸻

9. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Updates will be reflected by revising the “Effective Date” above.

⸻

